OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1779981070
OL,3,CMillions of Brits at risk of addiction
OL,4,Cto 'over the counter' medicines
OL,6,FAn exclusive survey conducted for
OL,7,FITV's Tonight programme, found that
OL,8,Fmore than one in three users of non-
OL,9,Fprescription codeine, could be at risk
OL,10,Fof addiction through use beyond the
OL,11,Fguidance period, as ITV News Reporter
OL,12,FSam Holder explains
OL,14,FAround 10 million people in the UK may
OL,15,Fhave put themselves at risk of
OL,16,Fdeveloping a dependency or addiction
OL,17,Fto codeine-based painkillers, a survey
OL,18,Fcarried out for ITV Tonight has
OL,19,Funcovered.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
